      "side": 1,
      "message": "We don\u0027t currently have a way to get the context of whether the current candidate is retrying a mishap at HEAD or if there were successes for later commits. I chose to assume there were later successes; otherwise retrying or bisecting mishaps would be prioritized higher than trying the same task spec at HEAD.\n\nI probably should have drawn the diagram like this:\n\n// Actual:    +- - - - -+  Pretend       +---------+  Pretend      +---------+\n//         c2 | ?????   |  before:   c2  | success |  after:   c2  | success |\n//            +---------+                |         |               +---------+\n//         c1 | mishap  |            c1  |         |           c1  | running |\n//            +---------+                +---------+               +---------+\n//\n// Bisect task with blamelist {c1, c2} at c1:\n// Actual:    +- - - - -+  Pretend       +---------+  Pretend      +---------+\n//         c3 | ?????   |  before    c3  | success |  after:   c3  | success |\n//            +---------+                |         |               |         |\n//         c2 | mishap  |            c2  |         |           c2  |         |\n//            |         |                |         |               +---------+\n//         c1 |         |            c1  |         |           c1  | running |\n//            +---------+                +---------+               +---------+",
